Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper is about language modeling and morphological analysis.
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper discusses the use of a language model and probes to analyze its learning.
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is relevant as the paper discusses the ability of the language model to learn abstract morphological regularities.
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is relevant as the paper discusses the use of a neural network-based language model.
- cs.SD (Sound) is less likely but still possible as the paper discusses the identification of word and morpheme boundaries, which could be related to speech processing.
